This is a **bug in the `useLocalStorage` hook**: 
- ✅ The page display shows the initial value correctly (100 messages)
- ❌ The initial value (100) is NOT written to localStorage on first render

The hook only reads from localStorage on first render (finding nothing, since the key doesn't exist), then falls back to the `initialValue` parameter (100) for in-memory state. But it doesn't write this initial value back to localStorage.

This behavior means that if the user refreshes the page without ever clicking the badge, the page will continue to show 100 (from the prop/initialValue) rather than the stored value - which defeats the purpose of persistence via localStorage.

